{
  "texts": [
    "This can be translated into the bosonized variables (2.19) viaσ2 (ϕ 1)(z) = ϕ 1 (z) -log z, σ2 (ϕ 2)(z) = ϕ 2 (z) + log z, σ2 (κ i)(z) = κ i (z),from which we deduce that σ2 (∂Φ) (z) = ∂Φ(z) is invariant.",
    "Since the OPE of ∂Φ(z) with ψ ± (u α) is trivial, we conclude that (5.5) must be regular as z → 0 and the OPE of ∂Φ(z) with W (u α) is trivial.",
    "We conclude that there are no poles at z = u α.",
    "Hidden poles of ∂φ(z).Is it possible for there to be other poles so far not accounted for?",
    "If there are any other poles in (5.4), they must come from non-insertion points, which is a consequence of working with the bosonized theory as we have seen before."
  ]
}